                <h1>Warsan Shire amplifies marginalized voices at poetry reading </h1>
                
                                    <figure class="dom-art-container my-4">
                                                    <img src="https://snworksceo.imgix.net/dtc/43ec0fac-1c4c-425e-ae09-3ac98320d469.sized-1000x1000.jpg?w=1000" alt="&lt;p&gt;British&#x20;poet&#x20;Warsan&#x20;Shire,&#x20;pictured&#x20;in&#x20;2010,&#x20;visited&#x20;Duke&#x20;in&#x20;April&#x20;to&#x20;read&#x20;some&#x20;of&#x20;her&#x20;works,&#x20;primarily&#x20;focusing&#x20;on&#x20;marginalized&#x20;voices.&#x20;&amp;nbsp&#x3B;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;" class="w-100">
                                                <div class="domphoto-caption mt-2 text-left text-md-right">
                            <p>British poet Warsan Shire, pictured in 2010, visited Duke in April to read some of her works, primarily focusing on marginalized voices. &nbsp;</p>

                                                             <aside class="photo-caption photo-credit d-block pl-1">
